data.name: label2.Text
data.value:
Right-Click on the Highlight-Tab or individual Group to Enable or Disable filters. - When the TAB is disabled, Serial Input is switched into Char-Read mode. - When the TAB is enabled, a line of data is read and displayed. - In char-read mode, partial data is displayed as it arrives.
Type in the RegEx to highlight the streaming text on console. - The RegEx must contain [one group], and only first group is highlighted. - E.g: ^Channel ([0-9]+), will highlight the channel number only.
RegEx is applied from RegEx1 to n in sequence. - Upon getting a match other groups are skipped.
RegEx highlighting may slow down the display, so only enable the required ones.
Examples: - ^Channel ([0-9]+) - (error|Error) - URL: ([^ ]+)$
Cursor/Focus on the message console area, when serial data is being received: - Will cause auto-scrolling, even when Autoscroll is turned off. - May cause wrong section of data to be highlighted by filters.
RegEx will work if selected Line Endings (CR, LF) match that of incoming data
Plot: - Enter regular expression which will extract the number from the data - Data is auto-ranged. - Type in Min/Max Y value in range boxes for manual range setting.
